# Plan Gate — KS Global Estates

## Review

### Checks performed
1. Read full planner.out (all sections + handoff).
2. Read pre-researcher.out handoff + image URL section to confirm research integration.
3. Spot-checked 3 of 25 Unsplash image URLs via HTTP HEAD (all returned 200).
4. Confirmed mn-state-park-tracker demo-src scaffold directory exists and is accessible.
5. Cross-checked all 11 R# requirements in brief.json against the traceability matrix.
6. Verified file budget, build config, state shape, and Leaflet init approach are present.

### Findings

**Pass criteria met:**
- All 11 R# mapped (10 demoed, 1 narrative). No requirement left unmapped.
- Design system fully specified: hex palette, Google Fonts URL, layout rules, motion spec, 28 anti-AI tells listed.
- Tech stack concrete: Vite + React 18 + Leaflet 1.9.4, CARTO tiles, build config with base + outDir, Leaflet StrictMode guard, DivIcon pin approach.
- App state schema specified (filters object, selectedProperty, detailProperty, view, favorites, filteredProperties/useMemo).
- 25 property mock DB schema defined; 25 Unsplash URLs confirmed live in pre-researcher.out.
- Scaffold source (mn-state-park-tracker demo-src) confirmed to exist.
- File budget 13 (1 over cap, justified in plan). All 13 files named with purpose.
- No unknowns flagged; planner self-assessed PLAN READY.
- No mw-backend or Surface runner dependency (frontend-only confirmed).

**Minor notes (non-blocking):**
- Mobile/responsive layout for split-pane is not explicitly specified (no breakpoint px value, no decision on map-vs-list tab pattern for narrow viewports). Mentioned in traceability ("responsive layout") but not designed. Builder will need to make this call independently; not a research gap.
- Hero image not pinned to a specific URL from the 25 — builder default is acceptable.
- workSamples.js entry field schema not spelled out, but builder can infer from existing entries.

None of these are planning unknowns or missing research; they are implementation details appropriately left to the builder.

